JavaScript, also called JS for short, is one of the most popular programming languages. 
JavaScript is a high-level, dynamic, object-oriented, and interpreted language that supports a variety of programming styles.
This language can be used for server side programming, mobile applications, games and desktop applications. 
Therefore, it can be considered that the JavaScript programming language is a versatile language.

In the world of programming languages, the role of JavaScript is like the role of a verb in a sentence

The first version of JavaScript was released by Brendan Echo in 1995,
and JavaScript has been updated 6 times to become today's JavaScript.

We have three ways to run JavaScript :
. Using console tab of web browsers 
. Using Node.js
. By creating web pages

We have two types of intializing variables : Var and Let
If you are sure that the value of a variable won't change throughout the program, it's recommended
to use const .


